wikipedia_page.main: George Nicol (28 December 1886 – 28 January 1967) was a British athlete.  He competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics in London at the 1912 Summer Olympics in Stockholm. He was born in Battersea.Nicol won his preliminary heat in the 400 metres with a time of 50.8 seconds.  This qualified him to compete in the semifinals, where he placed third in his heat to be eliminated.
